readables/man2/journal_thomas
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "2"
	"page1_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		"    I am going to be in so much trouble. Not been here a month, me, and already I’m in the kacky bucket. Why did I go and stick my nose in? "
		""
		"    They all been saying the cook’s got one foot in the grave already, so when I sees him packing rat poison in the larder with that look of death on his face, I get the most terrible feeling that something bad is to happen. So what did I do? I waited 'til he was gone, then I went "
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		"to pour that poison down the sink. But then I heard someone coming and I was so scared it might be Hales that I tossed it into the coal sacks in storage and hurried back to my room. "
		""
		"    Stupid Thomas, because when I went back the next day to find it, all the coal sacks was gone! And I don't know where they been taken. Where is all the coal being used in this place? I can’t ask the innkeeper cos he'll"
	}
	"page2_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		"want to know what I done, and I dare not ask Hales cos she'll show me where it is and I am not sure I really want to know. "
		""
		"    The cook doesn’t seem to have noticed yet, but soon he will. Oh why did I not just mind my own business? "
		""
	}
	"page2_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_right_body"	:
	{
		""
	}
