		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		"street to the back of the inn during the middle of the night. What sense is there in moving about at such an hour? And those rambunctious peasants continually add to the clatter by wailing and screaming as they climb aboard. The drunken fools. How are they able to wake in the morning after making merry so late into the night?"
		""
	}
	"page2_left_title"	:
