		"    Good, you've made it this far without arousing suspicion."
		"    Before he disappeared, Jacobs sent me a hurried note to report that the city's poor were being lured into the underbelly of this very inn after dark, never to be seen again."
		"    Can you imagine what fear might inspire a thief to reach out to the very Watch Officer who had on more than one occasion placed him in chains, and even interrogated him? Think on that."
		"    Well, it just so happens that street dwellers have indeed been going missing all across the city's slums of late, and Jacobs is not the first to have noticed. He is the first however to have identified one of the "
	}
	"page2_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_body"	:
	{
		""
		"holes into which they seem to have vanished."
		"    Jacobs specifically informed me of the room he had taken here, which is why I rented it myself and searched it thoroughly upon my arrival. Please take this key that he left behind and find out where it fits. He did not hide it here without good reason."
		"    Since my presence at the inn will have given cause to halt any untoward activities for the temporary duration of my stay, it is imperative that you now set about finding out what happened to Jacobs. He is a most vital witness."
		"    Also see what you can dig up about Lord Twistleton, who resides in the manor across "
	}
	"page3_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page3_body"	:
	{
		""
		"the street. The man is surely involved and no doubt keeps a journal."
	}
